### Installing software on debian based
APT -> ADVANCED PACKAGING TOOL

apt-get apt-cache were convined as a apt

apt search "name pacckage"
apt insstall package
apt remove package -> this command dont remove configuration
apt purge packgae

apt update -> uptade local list of remote repositories
apt upgrade -> uptade installed packages
apt autoremove -> sometimes packages need other packgaes to work, so if we run this command we are gonna deleted all that shity packages

dpgk help you with the things that you installed as .deb
